Ask HN: How Do You Keep Track of Your Favorite Recipes?
text:
Here is my dilemma:
Many of my favorite cooking recipes are spread across different formats: cookbooks, youtube videos, websites (that break their URLs often), and more. How do you keep track of/organize/compile all of your favorite recipes for posterity?

Ask HN: Have coding bootcamps killed the for-profit tech college?
text:
Or were they already dying out on their own? I remember Westwood being especially controversial. It's now been closed for years. So has ITT Tech, another big one. Yes, I know bootcamps are also for profit, but maybe their "leanness" has given them some benefits to thrive and become the more attractive and (in most cases) more affordable vocational option?

On the other hand I'm surprised DeVry has held out for as long as it has, and they had opened a new local campus about two years ago.

Ask HN: What would happen if Twitter shut down?
text:
I was just thinking, if Twitter shut down, it seems it would have a pretty sizable impact to a number of individuals and businesses.

I can think of many individuals and businesses that rely on Twitter for a nontrivial percentage of their income and traffic.

I imagine one or more apps would replace this, both existing and new. But it seems like this would take some time, especially for people (likely like myself) that aren’t on a lot of other platforms, and would be slow to migrate to something else.

I know this is a “who knows” question, but thought there could be some here that may have a reasonably thought-out prediction.
